Duration.description:
A Duration represents the elapsed time between two instants
as an int64 nanosecond count. The representation limits the
largest representable duration to approximately 290 years.

Har.description: Har is a container type for deserialization

comment.description: Optional. A comment provided by the user or the browser.

name.description: Required. The name of the browser that created the log.

version.description: Required. The version number of the browser that created the log.

HarCache.title: HarCache contains info about a request coming from browser cache.

comment.description: optional (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the application.
optional (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the application.

expires.description: optional - Expiration time of the cache entry.

hitCount.description: The number of times the cache entry has been opened.

lastAccess.description: The last time the cache entry was opened.

HarCacheObject.description: HarCacheObject is used by both beforeRequest and afterRequest

HarCookie.title: HarCookie contains list of all cookies (used in <request> and <response> objects).

comment.description: optional (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the application.

domain.description: optional The host of the cookie.

expires.description:
optional HarCookie expiration time.
(ISO 8601 YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sTZD, e.g. 2009-07-24T19:20:30.123+02:00).

httpOnly.description: optional Set to true if the cookie is HTTP only, false otherwise.

path.description: optional The path pertaining to the cookie.

secure.description:
optional (new in 1.2) True if the cookie was transmitted over ssl, false
otherwise.

comment.description: Optional. A comment provided by the user or the application.

name.description: Required. The name of the application that created the log.

version.description: Required. The version number of the application that created the log.

HarCreator.description: HarCreator contains information about the log creator application

HarEntry.title: HarEntry is a unique, optional Reference to the parent page.

comment.description: (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the application.

connection.description:
optional (new in 1.2) Unique ID of the parent TCP/IP connection, can be
the client port number. Note that a port number doesn't have to be unique
identifier in cases where the port is shared for more connections. If the
port isn't available for the application, any other unique connection ID
can be used instead (e.g. connection index). Leave out this field if the
application doesn't support this info.

serverIPAddress.description:
optional (new in 1.2) IP address of the server that was connected
(result of DNS resolution).

startedDateTime.description:
Date and time stamp of the request start
(ISO 8601 YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sTZD).

time.description:
Total elapsed time of the request in milliseconds. This is the sum of all
timings available in the timings object (i.e. not including -1 values) .

HarEntry.description: Leave out this field if the application does not support grouping by pages.

HarLog.title: HarLog represents the root of the exported data. This object MUST be present and its name MUST be "log".

comment.description:
Optional. A comment provided by the user or the application. Sorting
entries by startedDateTime (starting from the oldest) is preferred way how
to export data since it can make importing faster. However, the reader
application should always make sure the array is sorted (if required for
the import).

entries.description:
Required. An array of objects of type entry, each representing one
exported (tracked) HTTP request.

pages.description:
Optional. An array of objects of type page, each representing one exported
(tracked) page. Leave out this field if the application does not support
grouping by pages.

version.description: Required. Version number of the format.

HarPage.title: HarPage object for every exported web page and one <entry> object for every HTTP request.

comment.description: (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the application.

id.description: Unique identifier of a page within the . Entries use it to refer the parent page.

startedDateTime.description:
Date and time stamp for the beginning of the page load
(ISO 8601 YYYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss.sTZD, e.g. 2009-07-24T19:20:30.45+01:00).

HarPage.description:
In case when an HTTP trace tool isn't able to group requests by a page,
the <pages> object is empty and individual requests doesn't have a parent page.

HarPostData.title: HarPostData describes posted data, if any (embedded in <request> object).

comment.description:
optional (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the
application.

params.description: List of posted parameters (in case of URL encoded parameters).

HarPostParam.title: HarPostParam is a list of posted parameters, if any (embedded in <postData> object).

comment.description: optional (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the application.

contentType.description: optional content type of posted file.

fileName.description: optional name of a posted file.

value.description: optional value of a posted parameter or content of a posted file.

HarRequest.title: HarRequest contains detailed info about performed request.

bodySize.description:
Size of the request body (POST data payload) in bytes. Set to -1 if the
info is not available.

comment.description: (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the application.

headerSize.description:
Total number of bytes from the start of the HTTP request message until
(and including) the double CRLF before the body. Set to -1 if the info
is not available.

url.description: Absolute URL of the request (fragments are not included).

HarResponse.title: HarResponse contains detailed info about the response.

bodySize.description:
Size of the received response body in bytes. Set to zero in case of
responses coming from the cache (304). Set to -1 if the info is not
available.

comment.description: optional (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the application.

headersSize.description:
Total number of bytes from the start of the HTTP response message until
(and including) the double CRLF before the body. Set to -1 if the info is
not available.
The size of received response-headers is computed only from headers that
are really received from the server. Additional headers appended by the
browser are not included in this number, but they appear in the list of
header objects.

redirectURL.description: Redirection target URL from the Location response header.

HarResponseContent.title: HarResponseContent describes details about response content (embedded in <response> object).

_file.description:
optional (community enhancement) A path to an attached file containing this content
used by Playwright

comment.description: optional (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the application.

compression.description:
optional Number of bytes saved. Leave out this field if the information
is not available.

encoding.description:
optional (new in 1.2) Encoding used for response text field e.g
"base64". Leave out this field if the text field is HTTP decoded
(decompressed & unchunked), than trans-coded from its original character
set into UTF-8.

mimeType.description:
MIME type of the response text (value of the HarResponseContent-Type response
header). The charset attribute of the MIME type is included (if
available).

size.description:
Length of the returned content in bytes. Should be equal to
response.bodySize if there is no compression and bigger when the content
has been compressed.

text.description:
optional HarResponse body sent from the server or loaded from the browser
cache. This field is populated with textual content only. The text field
is either HTTP decoded text or encoded (e.g. "base64") representation of
the response body. Leave out this field if the information is not
available.

ListenType.title: ListenType defines the kind of script attached to an event.

NVP.description: NVP is simply a name/value pair with a comment

PageTiming.title: PageTiming describes timings for various events (states) fired during the page load.

comment.description: (new in 1.2) A comment provided by the user or the application.

onContentLoad.description:
HarResponseContent of the page loaded. Number of milliseconds since page load started
(page.startedDateTime). Use -1 if the timing does not apply to the current
request.
Depending on the browser, onContentLoad property represents DOMContentLoad
event or document.readyState == interactive.

onLoad.description:
HarPage is loaded (onLoad event fired). Number of milliseconds since page
load started (page.startedDateTime). Use -1 if the timing does not apply
to the current request.

PageTiming.description: All times are specified in milliseconds. If a time info is not available appropriate field is set to -1.

PageTimings.title: PageTimings describes various phases within request-response round trip.

comment.description:
optional (new in 1.2) - Time required for SSL/TLS negotiation. If this
field is defined then the time is also included in the connect field (to
ensure backward compatibility with HAR 1.1). Use -1 if the timing does not
apply to the current request.

connect.description:
optional - DNS resolution time. The time required to resolve a host name.
Use -1 if the timing does not apply to the current request.

dns.description:
optional - Time spent in a queue waiting for a network connection. Use -1
if the timing does not apply to the current request.

receive.description: Waiting for a response from the server.

send.description:
optional - Time required to create TCP connection. Use -1 if the timing
does not apply to the current request.

ssl.description: Time required to read entire response from the server (or cache).

wait.description: Time required to send HTTP request to the server.

PageTimings.description: All times are specified in milliseconds.

PostmanRequest.title: A PostmanRequest represents an HTTP request.

PostmanResponse.title: A PostmanResponse represents an HTTP response.

PostmanURL.title: PostmanURL is a struct that contains an PostmanURL in a "broken-down way".
